    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It's not clear to me either, but I think I prefer underscore for `internal` functions as well. In that case the information that we want to convey is \"this is not externally reachable\".\r\n\r\nLeaving out the underscore in internal functions makes sense if what we want to convey with underscores is \"this is neither part of the internal nor external API, so do not use it\", but for that purpose we can already use `private` functions which mean exactly that, and are statically checked.",
